<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2017_01">

<p>Hail! Prosperity! <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the 4th year of king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō</foreign></supplied> Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ. In this year, for Mahādeva of Tirunettānam, for a lamp <supplied reason="subaudible">for?; on behalf?; by?</supplied> Varaguṇa Mahārāja, 200 <foreign>kācu </foreign>were taken <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>koṇṭa</foreign></supplied> through the hand <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaivaḻi</foreign></supplied> of our queen <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nampirāṭṭiyār</foreign></supplied>, 100 <foreign>kācu </foreign>were taken <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>koṇṭa</foreign></supplied> through the hand <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaivaḻi</foreign></supplied> of king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōṉ</foreign></supplied> Parāntakaṉ, 120 <foreign>kācu </foreign>were given <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> through <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaḻi</foreign></supplied> Vēḷāḷaṉ of Veṇpanāṭu; with these, we will supply <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṭṭuvōmāṉōm</foreign></supplied> everyday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicati</foreign></supplied> four <foreign>nāḻi </foreign><supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāṉāḻi</foreign></supplied> of ghee <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ney</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>nārācanāḻi </foreign><supplied reason="explanation">a measure</supplied>, having brought <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṇantu</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">it</supplied> to the sacred temple itself <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrīkōyilukkēy</foreign></supplied>, we the Sabhā of the two quarters <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iraṇṭu cēri</foreign></supplied> of Paṉaiyūr.</p></div>

